<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="997" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d997">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.731/376a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Counselor for the Department of
                                    State</gloss> to the British Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRSCA1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Spring
                                Rice</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1915</hi>
                                </date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Ambassador</hi>: May I again call your
                            attention to the seriousness of the interruption by the British censors
                            of strictly commercial cablegrams pertaining to non-contraband goods
                            exchanged between this country and other neutral countries, especially
                            Scandinavian countries.</p>
                        <p>It would be most gratifying if I could have your assistance in an effort
                            to bring about some arrangement with your Government whereby the relief
                            which is needed so much, not only by the United States but by the other
                            neutral countries, may be obtained.</p>
                        <p>I should be very glad to discuss this matter with you whenever you can
                            conveniently call on me, and remain [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>